@endnode

@node "9_2" " SECTION 9 - Miscellaneous "
 2] My rendering times and even my refresh times in the editors are much MUCH
too slow, even with an accelerator. Is there any basic tricks or hints that are
often overlooked that might help me out?"

Always be sure to MERGE your objects. This eliminates multiple faces, points and
lines. Some objects have a VERY large number of these and it can slow your times
down by up to 1/2!

                        ------------------------------
                        @{"... Please Return to News  ..." link "NEW" }
                        @{"... Please Return to Index ..." link "INDEX" }
                        ------------------------------
@endnode

@node "9_3" " SECTION 9 - Miscellaneous "
 3] When does one get good enough so that they don't render ugly pictures!

Practice with a simple objects (to cut down trace time) over and over and over.
Varying lighting & color etc.  This will allow you to get the effect you want
which is only a technical problem.

